SUMMARY:Improv Greenhouse
DESCRIPTION:Get ready to be surprised\, delighted\, and maybe even see your wildest idea take on a life of its own!\n\n\n\nGraduate Greenhouse is a Wednesday night showcase featuring alumni from Unexpected Productions Improv School. Each performance highlights a different alumni group\, putting their training to the test with unpredictable scenes\, various formats\, and improvised stories. From long-form storytelling to character work\, these performers explore the boundaries of improv. \nJan 7 Market Improv \nJan 14 \nJan 21 \nBut the fun doesn’t stop there! Stick around for a double feature as we roll into Seattle’s longest-running Improv Open Mic: the Duos Open Mic! Starting at 8:00 pm\, this weekly showcase promises even more laughs\, surprises\, and improv magic.
URL:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/event/graduate-greenhouse-fka-an-improvised-holiday-special-2-2-2/2026-04-01/
LOCATION:Unexpected Productions\, 1428 Post Alley at the Gum Wall in Pike Place Market\, Seattle\, WA\, 98101\, United States
ATTACH;FMTTYPE=image/jpeg:https://www.unexpectedproductions.org/wp-content/uploads/2026/01/611744788_25834828646123545_7391804144568306027_n.jpg
END:VEVENT
